accreditation represents our programs having curriculum which meets rigorous standards, that our programs qualify our students to practice at their degree level, that our programs have established and adhere to reasonable policies and procedures, and that san jos state university lends its support. this process is similar to the joint commission accreditation that hospitals strive to achieve.thebaccalaureate degreeprogram in nursing, themaster's degree programsin nursing, and thedoctor of nursing practiceprogram at san jos state university are accredited by the commission on collegiate nursing education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).the wound and ostomy education programat the valley foundation school of nursing is accredited by thewound, ostomy and continence nursing society (wocn).additionally, san jos state university is accredited by thewestern association of schools and colleges (wasc).phone:408-924-3131fax:408-924-3135email:nursing@sjsu.edugive tothe school of nursing